  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: If view profile of another contact then Status field with more than 3 lines can't be scrolled down. Only on Android.\r\n![status profile](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/6584810/25593989/3b0f7744-2ebf-11e7-8cf3-0e71aff1b0e4.png)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\nStatus field in profile can be scrolled\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\nStatus field in profile can't be scrolled\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\nVideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0Bz3t9zSg1wb7UG1DUXQ2VnB2VlU\r\nYou need to have 1-1 chat with a contact who has very long status (max length allowed)\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1-1 chat \r\n- Tap on profile picture in top right corner\r\n- Tap on Status field to scroll it\r\n- Try to scroll to the last line\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\r\n* Status version: 0.9.6 and later (0.9.7d34)\r\n* Operating System: Android only\r\n\r\n",
